<br>
And pet will zone with you IF you have the pet icon up, its that buff that causes pet to &quot;zone&quot; with you, basically what happens is that when you zone in you get a new warder for free if you have the buff, if you dont you wont get it. Before the buff killed the pet if it faded (either by timing out or you clicking it). Now it doesnt kill pet when fading so you can click it off if you need an extra slot or want to make sure the pet dont zone with you (or comes back as a green pet when you LD).<br>
<br>
Like I said in another thread, since they changed the pet aggro rules its not so useful to not getting the pet back if you LD, but if your fighting mobs which has loads of green buddies that dont help you might want to click the buff off. Since if you LD while fighting and then log back in and get reaggrod by the non greens that you where fighting pet will jump in and is suddenly fair game for the greens, which will slaughter it and then turn on you to slowly pound you into the ground..<br>
Not useful often but I think its better the way it is, then you have the choice. Besides, it makes sure you wont loose pet once the buff wears off. <p>Dannor Stoutwise 42 cleric<BR>
Dahkar 26 beastlord<BR>
